title: Lexington knocks off Gering in first round of district tourney
text:
JEFF FIELDER/Star-Herald Lexington knocks off Gering in first round of district tourney 
Gering's Kaetlyn Todd hits during a Class B, District 6 Softball Tournament game against Lexington on Thursday in North Platte. Lexington knocks off Gering in first round of district tourney JEFF FIELDER Sports Editor jfielder@starherald.com Star Herald NORTH PLATTE - The Gering softball team surged ahead 5-0, but Lexington came back to register a 12-7 victory in their opening game of the Class B, District 6 Tournament on Thursday at North Platte. The Bulldogs jumped out to a 4-0 lead in the second inning and then increased their advantage to 5-0 after three innings.   Remember me on this computer Login   Subscription required
